# Codex CLI configuration for AI-MarketTracker

version: 1
name: AI-MarketTracker
description: Codex CLI rules and context; AGENTS.md is the source of truth.

context:
  - AGENTS.md
  - README.md
  - docs/proweleu-brain/README.md
  - docs/proweleu-brain/RUNBOOK.md

rules:
  - Follow Non-Negotiables in AGENTS.md §1.
  - Enforce directory contracts from AGENTS.md §3.
  - All APIs must have TypeScript types or Zod schemas and remain backward-compatible.
  - No secrets in code; use environment variables or local secret managers.
  - All changes must update docs (README, AGENTS.md, or /docs).

guardrails:
  - Do not alter trade evaluation logic without explicit approval.
  - Do not change GPT prompt format without explicit approval.
  - Do not change MongoDB field structures without explicit approval.

workspace:
  root: .
  expected_top_level:
    - client/
    - server/
    - docs/
    - proweleu-brain/
    - AGENTS.md

task_templates:
  - title: Wire Polygon MCP + REST fallback
    path: server/src/services/mcp-clients/polygon
    checklist:
      - Create client.ts calling Polygon MCP tools
      - Add restFallback.ts for missing endpoints
      - Add adapter.ts to normalize to DTOs
      - Include unit tests for both paths
  - title: Implement SPX chain fetch + delta filter
    path: server/src/services/orchestrator
    checklist:
      - Fetch SPX options chain
      - Compute deltas, select OTM 20→12
      - Return candidate spreads with credits
      - Check min OI and max spread width
  - title: RAG retriever
    path: server/src/services/rag/retriever.ts
    checklist:
      - Use Atlas Vector Search with filters {ticker, doc_type, date_range}
      - topK=12 with recency bias
      - Add tests using fixtures
  - title: LLM deep path
    path: server/src/services/llm-router
    checklist:
      - Build system+context prompt
      - Enforce JSON schema from AGENTS.md §5.1
      - Use vLLM OpenAI-compatible endpoint
  - title: proweleu-brain compose
    path: proweleu-brain/
    checklist:
      - Add docker-compose for Mongo, Redis, gateway, rag, llm, mcp
      - Add healthchecks and depends_on
      - Auto-index knowledge on startup

acceptance_checks:
  - Unit tests for DTO validators and JSON schema pass
  - Integration tests for MCP adapter and RAG pass
  - LLM path produces valid JSON per §5.1 (no extra prose)
  - Logs include Pino JSON with requestId and key metrics

logging:
  standard: pino
  format: json

security:
  secrets_in_code: false
  env_required: true
